==English==

===Noun===
'''outfit'''  ([[outfits]])

#a set of [[clothing]] (with accessories)
#: ''She wore a fashionable '''outfit''' with matching purse and shoes.''
#any [[cohesive]] unit such as a [[military]] [[company]] 
#[[gear]] consisting of a set of articles or [[tool]]s for a specified purpose
#(informal) a [[business]] or [[firm]]
#:''Should we buy it here, or do you think the '''outfit''' across town will have a better deal?''

====Translations====
*Finnish: [[vaatekerta]] (1), [[puku]] (1), [[varusteet]] (3), [[setti]] (3)

====Synonyms====
*[[kit]]
*[[getup]] (1)
*[[rig]]
*[[turnout]]

===Verb===
'''outfit'''
#to [[provide]] with (something) usually for a specific purpose
#: "The expedition was '''outfitted''' with proper clothing, food, and other necessities"

====Translations====
*Finnish: [[varustaa]] (1)

====Synonyms====
